	<h1>gokul gowri thinks about biomolecules and bits</h1>

  <br>

  <h2><span style="font-style:normal">üíΩ üåø </span> welcome <span style="font-style:normal"> üåª üß¨</span></h2>
  <br>

  I'm a PhD student in the Molecular Systems lab at the Wyss Institute and Harvard Systems Biology.
  <br>
  <br>

  Conceptually, I'm interested in the relationship between biology and computation. How do biological systems encode and process information? How can complex biological systems be represented and explored using silicon computers?
  <br>
  <br>

  More concretely, I've spent time thinking about chemical reaction networks, DNA barcodes, single cell measurements, and information measures.

  <br>
  <br>
  <a href="http://github.com/ggdna/">github</a></li> \\ <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=sJJAZjoAAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao">google scholar</a> \\  <a href="https://last.fm/user/gokulgowri">last.fm</a>

